gs into (early) Hellenistic times. This has consequences firstly for the understanding of the letter as an historical document, but then also for those historical models which seek to explain the genesis of the Torah principally from Ezra 7.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aArtaxerxes. 4aEsra (Buch). 4aGesetz (Theol.). 4aSchenkung. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI0 cprintz978311017967540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090099640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110900996423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110900996/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014